As an introverted, privacy-conscious self-employed creative individual, running a business shouldn't feel this awkward, but sometimes it does. Most online resources and mentors tell you to interact with large (evil) tech companies in an extroverted way. Here, advertise, follow the algorithm, share your personal charm. Get verified on that platform, stay online 24/7, answer questions with your own videos, and respond immediately. Videos, videos, and videos again.
1/3
This year is my year of transformation for me.
I don't want to keep giving my money, data, and energy to large tech companies anymore, nor do I want to listen to mentors who only offer a single extroverted solution for everyone. I'm exploring new business models, while also working to overcome my long-held belief that only a certain way of doing things leads to success.
Wishing me luck!
The first step has been taken.
I have left FB, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and logged out of my personal WhatsApp account.
Yesterday, I also removed the last external tracker - Google Analytics - from my website, and it feels great.
Recently, I subscribed to a European CRM service to better support GDPR, and I will be migrating my business over the next few weeks.
I have transferred my MX records to Proton, now having full SPF, DKIM, and DMARC without needing to pay Google for basic email verification.
3/3
