Website: You can check out @user5. It looks easy to use and has a beautiful interface, and it's open source. I plan to migrate one of my websites to it before my next renewal.
Signal: Check out cal.com. It's an open source calendar service that integrates scheduling for video calls with Element, Jitsi, etc. It also supports Signal, but I haven't tested whether it's only for messaging or also for video calls.
I can recommend @user6. End-to-end encryption, decentralized, and open source.
